"Here no one will be judged," says one of the employees of RPG Byty and a man who is on the street in front of the customer service center gives him at least in part the reason.
"I receive a pension of 13,000 and I have 5,000 left for food; I have no means to go to the courts," she says.
But, immediately, the employee sows doubt.
"We'll see."
