EU changes rules to get visas
People should go to Visa Applicants Service centres prior to their interview in the Consular Section; the cost will be lower and as well as the waiting time.
As of 10 January 2011, the procedure to process a visa at the U.S. Embassy and consulates will be changed.
Under the new procedure, most applicants should attend Visa Applicants Service (ASC) centres before their interview in the Consular Section.
ASC staff shall take biometric information from the applicant, which shall be reviewed by the Consular Section prior to the interview.
The new procedure will have certain advantages for the aspirants, including:
The total cost of processing the visa will be lower, no longer will be necessary to make a payment to make the appointment, another payment to process the visa application and another for the messaging service to deliver the document.
The applicant will only make a single payment that will cover the three services.
The current rate will remain unchanged: the equivalent of $140 for a tourist visa, $150 for visa cases on request (including temporary worker visas) and $390 for trade and investor visas.
People wishing to renew their visas will not have to attend an interview with the Consular Officer, but will only go to the nearest AUC where they will present their documents and take their tracks.
Due to the fact that biometric information will be taken at the AUC, applicants who require a second appointment to be interviewed in the Consular Section will remain at this time less than in the past.
Also, those applying for visas in the Consulates in Ciudad Juárez, Monterrey and Nuevo Laredo will no longer pay the extra service fee of 26 dollars.
For further information on the new visa application procedure, please visit the following page: http://mexico.usembassy.gov/boletines/sp101201_Visas-FAQs.html
